    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.16.4-6_0001"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">4</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">JOSEPH PULITZER
                        <lb/>
                    ST LOUIS POST DISPATCH
                        <lb/>
                    ST LOUIS MO</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>March 7, 1933.</dateline>
                    
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Branson, Missouri.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>As Mr. Stokes suggests, I am glad to enclose his letter concerning your review of his Paul Bunyan. Congratulations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Joseph Pulitzer</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="enclosure">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.16.4-6_0002"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">5</fw>
                
                <note type="unknown"><unclear>Mr.</unclear><hi rend="caps">N.</hi>   1st  <hi rend="caps">JP</hi></note>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">RICHARD L. STOKES
                        <lb/>
                    321 EAST 72ND STREET
                        <lb/>
                    NEW YORK</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>Feb. 3, 1933</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Pulitzer:</salute> 
                </opener>
                <p>Truly, the Post-Dispatch continues to be an extraordinary newspaper! Of the <unclear>scores</unclear> of reviews my "Paul Bunyan" has received all over the country, Mr. Neihardt's seems to me by far the most understanding and penetrating: Please convey to him my gratitude and compliments. No other critic has seen so clearly the social 
                
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.16.4-6_0003"/>
                    <fw type="curatorial"><del>5</del><add>6</add></fw>
                
                    satire underlying the <unclear>framework</unclear> of comedy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>With cordial regards, I am,</salute> 
                    <salute>Very sincerely yours,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Richard L. Stokes</signed>
                
                    <note>Joseph Pulitzer, Esq.</note>
                </closer>                
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
